column2: writes        The total number of region entries that have been written to disk. A write is done every time an entry is created on disk or every time its value is modified on disk.
column3: writeTime        The total amount of time spent writing to disk
column4: writtenBytes        The total number of bytes that have been written to disk
column5: reads        The total number of region entries that have been read from disk
column6: readTime        The total amount of time spent reading from disk
column7: readBytes        The total number of bytes that have been read from disk
column8: removes        The total number of region entries that have been removed from disk
column9: removeTime        The total amount of time spent removing from disk
column10: entriesOnlyOnDisk        The current number of entries whose value is on disk and is not in memory. This is true of overflowed entries. It is also true of recovered entries that have not yet been faulted in.
column11: bytesOnlyOnDisk        The current number bytes on disk and not in memory. This is true of overflowed entries. It is also true of recovered entries that have not yet been faulted in.
column12: entriesInVM        The current number of entries whose value resides in the VM. The value may also have been written to disk.
column13: writesInProgress        current number of oplog writes that are in progress
column14: localInitializations        The number of times that this region has been initialized solely from the local disk files (0 or 1)
column15: remoteInitializations        The number of times that this region has been initialized by doing GII from a peer (0 or 1)
